<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[120,1225,1311,1786]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
ETYMOLOGY: The epithet is from the Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[787,844,1572,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis">
<emphasis box="[787,844,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “strong,” and refers to the more robust body shape compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Koteja and Azar" authorityYear="2008" box="[605,731,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[605,731,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">A. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[790,952,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName authority="Vea &amp; Grimaldi, 2015" authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[790,947,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitenuis" status="n. sp.">A. longitenuis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[959,1021,1610,1636]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[120,1225,1311,1786]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
DIAGNOSIS: 
<emphasis box="[315,516,1647,1673]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName authority="Vea &amp; Grimaldi, 2015" authorityName="Vea &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2015" box="[315,512,1647,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis" status="n. sp.">Apticoccus fortis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[526,593,1648,1674]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[836,1016,1647,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Electrococcidae" genus="Apticoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[836,959,1647,1673]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Apticoccus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: head very short, thorax wide, abdomen pear shaped, tergites wide and tapered posteriorly, penial sheath round with one pair of short setae, then abruptly thin and curved (ca. 1/5 body length).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
